Examine the autocorrelation function (ACF) and partial autocorrelation function (PACF) plots to identify the model orders: if ACF decays slowly and PACF cuts off at lag k, suggest AR(k); if PACF decays slowly and ACF cuts off at lag k, suggest MA(k). For a 200-point series, start with candidate models ARMA(1,1), ARMA(2,1), ARMA(1,2), and ARMA(2,2). Use AIC or BIC to select the best model—lower values indicate better fit. Alternatively, use grid search over p,q ∈ {0,1,2,3,4,5} and compare information criteria. Validate with residual diagnostics (white noise tests, ACF of residuals). A typical choice for stationary series this size is ARMA(1,1) or ARMA(2,1) unless ACF/PACF patterns suggest otherwise.